   {:e #blake3 "39a7eb9ffdb376e4113ba2c743c422e5188a4a8a49672f0128a2a218c4def9be" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Complete test suite for C9 covering BOTH paths: proactive (seed convergent findings) and reactive (observe subcommands). Must prove the original problem is solved: an agent can synthesize accumulated observations without reading external documents. UNIT TESTS FOR C9-P5 (observe subcommands, in concept.rs or observe.rs test section): (A) all_observations empty store returns empty vec. (B) all_observations with 5 observations returns 5 sorted by timestamp descending. (C) all_observations extracts correct fields (confidence, category, concept, title). (D) observe list renders all observations. (E) observe search filters by substring. (F) observe show displays full entity. (G) observe recent limits output. (H) observe TEXT creation still works (backward compat regression test). UNIT TESTS FOR C9-P4 (agent identity, in mod.rs or main.rs test section): (A) Default agent with no env var produces PID-based name. (B) BRAID_AGENT env var overrides PID. (C) Explicit --agent overrides env var. INTEGRATION TEST (tests/c9_second_order.rs — EXTEND existing): (A) Multi-agent test: 3 AgentIds, each observes same finding, find_agreement_clusters returns cluster with 3 agents, seed orientation contains Convergent findings section. (B) Observe subcommands test: create 5 observations, all_observations returns 5, search filters correctly. E2E SCRIPT (scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh): (1) braid init in temp dir. (2) Create 3 observations with different BRAID_AGENT env vars about same topic. (3) Create 1 unrelated observation. (4) braid observe list — assert 4 total. (5) braid observe search 'stagnant' — assert >= 2 matches. (6) braid observe recent 2 — assert exactly 2. (7) braid observe show ENTITY — assert full body displayed. (8) braid seed --task 'synthesize' — assert Convergent findings present with 3/3 agents. (9) All exit codes 0. All outputs logged with timestamps. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: On any assertion failure, dump: store datom count, observation count per agent, agreement cluster details, seed output in full, observe list output in full. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/tests/c9_second_order.rs, scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh, inline tests in concept.rs and observe.rs. DEPENDS-ON: C9-P4 (t-266f06d5), C9-P5 (t-3115acf1). EFFORT: 5h." :op :assert}
